Global Contrast Normalization

Reference: Deep Learning book (section 12.2.1.1 pg.455)

Prevents images from having varying amount of contrast. $$ X^\prime_{i,j,k} = s \frac{X_{i,j,k} - \overline{X}}{max\{\epsilon,\sqrt{\lambda+\frac{1}{3rc}\sum^c_{i=1} \sum^r_{j=1} \sum^3_{k=1}(X_{i,j,k}-\overline{X})^2} \}} $$

{% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %}

class GlobalContrastNorm[source]

GlobalContrastNorm(s=1, eps=1e-08, lmbda=0.0, decode_norm=True) :: Transform

prevents images from having varying contrast reference: Deep Learning book (section 12.2.1.1 pg.455) decodes used for show_batch, not to reverse the transform.

{% endraw %}

Examples

1. RGB No transforms

{% raw %} 
ds = Datasets(get_image_files(path/'train'),Pipeline(base_pipe[:-1]))
dls = TfmdDL(ds, bs=64,after_item=IntToFloatTensor,after_batch=Normalize.from_stats(*cifar_stats),device='cuda')
dls.show_batch(max_n=4)
{% endraw %}

2. RGB Global Contrast Normalization

{% raw %} 
dl2 = TfmdDL(ds,bs=64,after_item=IntToFloatTensor,after_batch=[Normalize.from_stats(*cifar_stats),GlobalContrastNorm],device='cuda')
dl2.show_batch(max_n=4)
{% endraw %}

3. Grayscale

{% raw %} 
ds_bw = Datasets(get_image_files(path/'train'),Pipeline([PILImageBW.create,ToTensor]))
dls_bw = TfmdDL(ds_bw, bs=64,after_item=IntToFloatTensor,after_batch=Normalize.from_stats(*cifar_stats),device='cuda')
dls_bw.show_batch(max_n=4)
{% endraw %}

4. Grayscale Global Contrast Normalization

{% raw %} 
dls_bw2 = TfmdDL(ds_bw, bs=64,after_item=IntToFloatTensor,after_batch=[Normalize.from_stats(*cifar_stats),GlobalContrastNorm],device='cuda')
dls_bw2.show_batch(max_n=4)
{% endraw %}

ZCA Whitening

Used to enhance edges

Wrapping kornia implementation in fastai transforms

(Currently it requires installing kornia from sources)

{% raw %} 
zca_block = ZCAWhitening(compute_inv=True)
{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %}

Wrapping kornia implementation
